      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p><i>cis</i>-1,2-Dichloroethylene and <i>trans</i>-1,2-dichloroethylene are <i>isomers,</i> compounds with the same formula but different chemical structures. Look at the following electrostatic potential maps, and tell whether either compound has a dipole moment.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbHNRIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--cacba1efc39f7497c29e8db79a939b8b3b4340c2/OChem_02_EC_003.jpg\" alt=\"The structural formulas and electrostatic potential maps of cis-1, 2-dichloroethylene and trans-1,2-dichloroethylene.\">",
